There is only one square where the king is safe. I did not found a checkmate for this continuation, but the advantage of the Black camp is too strong to do something great. 

After 31. Kb2, we have:
31. Kb2 Rc2+
32. Ka3 Bf8+
33. Be7 Bxe7#

If they play 32. Ka1, 32. ... b2+ may give you everything white camp has.
